Peter,

    The one major problem I see with your solution is that it
requires a centralized administration of user names, and a major
league user data at the central host, (e.g. Stanford.EDU) so
you know how to reach 'smith' when his mail hits the central
machine.  

    I also wonder if keeping this database up to date isn't more
effort than having mailers on workstations use user%workstation@nic-known-host.

Craig Partridge
CSNET Technical Staff

